"title": "1155: God, truthfulness of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1155: god, truthfulness of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>To call the LORD “the true God” means that he alone has in his being the fulness of deity and is worthy to be worshipped as God. He and his word are a trustworthy foundation for life because he speaks the truth and is utterly reliable and consistent in his character, his revelation of himself, his promises and his pronouncements.</p>\n<h2>Titles reflecting God's truthfulness</h2>\n<h3>The true God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:3\">2CH 15:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:10\">JER 10:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:9\">1TH 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>The God of truth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:5\">PSA 31:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:16\">ISA 65:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is ``the truth''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:17\">JHN 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:32\">JHN 6:32</a> <em>Jesus Christ calls himself “the true bread” meaning that he is real, substantial, reliable and life-giving</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:20\">1JN 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:7\">REV 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:14\">REV 3:14</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit of truth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:17\">JHN 14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26\">JHN 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:13\">JHN 16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:6\">1JN 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:6\">1JN 5:6</a></p>\n<h2>God is true to his character and his word</h2>\n<h3>He speaks the truth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:19\">ISA 45:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:28\">2SA 7:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:4\">PSA 33:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:160\">PSA 119:160</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:17\">JHN 17:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:5\">REV 21:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:6\">REV 22:6</a></p>\n<h3>He does not lie</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:19\">NUM 23:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:4\">ROM 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:13\">2TI 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:2\">TIT 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:18\">HEB 6:18</a></p>\n<h3>He is true to himself and his promises</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:4\">DEU 32:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:10\">PSA 25:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:4\">PSA 33:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:13\">PSA 145:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:6\">PSA 146:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:23\">LAM 3:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:13\">2TI 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>The truthfulness of God undergirds the law</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:142\">PSA 119:142</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:7\">PSA 19:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:151\">PSA 119:151</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:160\">PSA 119:160</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:6-Mal2:7\">MAL 2:6–2:7</a></p>\n<h2>The truthfulness of God undergirds the covenant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:10\">PSA 25:10</a></strong> <em>The Hebrew word translated “faithful” can also be translated “true”. The word is particularly associated with God steadfastly upholding his covenant promises.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:13\">PSA 145:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:19-Hos2:20\">HOS 2:19–2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:13\">2TI 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>The truthfulness of God undergirds the prophetic word</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:25\">EZK 12:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:11\">ISA 55:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:12\">JER 1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:9\">JER 28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:33\">EZK 33:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:45\">DAN 2:45</a></p>\n<h2>The truthfulness of God undergirds his promises</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:14-Josh23:15\">JOS 23:14–23:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:19\">NUM 23:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:20\">1KI 8:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:42\">PSA 105:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:20-Rom4:21\">ROM 4:20–4:21</a></p>\n<h2>The truthfulness of God undergirds his judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:13\">PSA 96:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:9\">PSA 98:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:3-Isa11:5\">ISA 11:3–11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:2\">ROM 2:2</a></p>\n<h2>The truthfulness of God undergirds the teaching of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:17\">JHN 1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:18\">MAT 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:16\">MAT 22:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:14\">MRK 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:21\">LUK 20:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:28\">MRK 3:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:24\">LUK 4:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:51\">JHN 1:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:31-John8:32\">JHN 8:31–8:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:37\">JHN 18:37</a></p>",
